  "intro": "Le Jugement de Midas (The Judgement of Midas) is a French com\u00e9die m\u00eal\u00e9e d'ariettes (a kind of op\u00e9ra comique), in three acts by Andr\u00e9 Gr\u00e9try first performed on 28 March 1778 in the apartments of Madame de Montesson at the Palais-Royal in Paris. The libretto is by the Irish playwright Thomas Hales (also known by the French name Thomas d'H\u00e8le) with additional contributions by Louis Anseaume. It was based on the burlesque opera Midas (1760) by Kane O'Hara."
